SOFTWARE.</pre>
          </section>

          <!-- What You Can Do -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl text-solana-green font-bold mb-4">├─ What You Can Do</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">Under the MIT License, you are free to:</p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>├─ <strong>Use:</strong> Use the software for any purpose, private or commercial</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>Copy:</strong> Make copies of the software</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>Modify:</strong> Change the software for any reason</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>Distribute:</strong> Share the original software or your modifications</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>Sublicense:</strong> Grant rights to others under the same terms</li>
              <li>└─ <strong>Private Use:</strong> Use and modify the software without disclosing changes</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Conditions -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl text-solana-green font-bold mb-4">├─ Conditions</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">When using SolCoder, you must:</p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>├─ <strong>License Notice:</strong> Include a copy of the MIT license and copyright notice</li>
              <li>└─ <strong>State Changes:</strong> Indicate any modifications made to the original code</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Limitations -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl text-solana-green font-bold mb-4">├─ Limitations</h2>
            <p class="mb-3">The MIT License comes with important limitations:</p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>├─ <strong>No Warranty:</strong> The software is provided "as is" without warranties</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>No Liability:</strong> The authors are not liable for any damage or issues</li>
              <li>├─ <strong>No Trademark Rights:</strong> The license does not grant rights to trademarks</li>
              <li>└─ <strong>No Patent Rights:</strong> Unless expressly stated by the licensor</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Why MIT -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl text-solana-green font-bold mb-4">├─ Why MIT License?</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 ml-4 border-l border-solana-green/30 pl-4">
              <p>
                The MIT License is one of the most permissive open-source licenses. We chose it because it:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-none space-y-2 ml-4">
                <li>├─ Allows commercial use without restrictions</li>
                <li>├─ Promotes innovation and collaboration</li>
                <li>├─ Is simple and easy to understand</li>
                <li>├─ Is compatible with other licenses</li>
                <li>└─ Respects the freedom and rights of all users</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Resources -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl text-solana-green font-bold mb-4">├─ Resources</h2>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>├─ <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-solana-purple hover:text-solana-green transition-colors">Official MIT License at OpenSource.org</a></li>
